AGI - Russian troops launched a large-scale attack with drones and cruise missiles > against Ukraine in the night, damaging energy infrastructure in various regions of the country. Kyiv Independent reported it.
&nbsp;
At least four people were injured, including a 7-year-old girl, in an attack in the city of Nikopol> in the Dnipropetrovsk oblast, where two buildings and a bus were hit. The scraps of a damaged Russian drone caused a fire in a crucial infrastructural structure in the Vinnytsia oblast, while in the Zaporizhzhia region a dozen buildings were hit but there were no injuries.
&nbsp;
"The Russian invaders launched a powerful attack on crucial infrastructures in various regions of Ukraine, using air, marine and terrestrial missiles, as well as drones of type Shahed",&nbsp; reported to Ukrinform Mykola Oleshchuk, commander of the Ukrainian military air force. &nbsp;35 cruise missiles and 46 drones were shot down, he added.
&nbsp;
Ukrainian Energy Minister Herman Halushchenko > has confirmed that energy infrastructure in the oblast of Zaporizhzhia, Dnipropetrovsk, Donetsk, Kirovohrad and Ivano-Frankivsk have been attacked and are evaluating and repairing damage.
&nbsp;
On Friday, Russian forces attacked the Ukrainian Oblast of Sumy 131 times in 24 separate attacks throughout the day, writes The Kiyv Independent reporting sources of the regional military administration .
&nbsp;
The communities of Khotin, Yunakivka, Krasnopillia, Velyka Pysarivka, Myropillia, Seredyna-Buda, Mykolaiv, Svesy and Esman were targeted.<br> Throughout the day, Russia assaulted border villages with attacks of mortars, drones and artillery, also launching explosives from drones on two communities. Victims or wounded were not reported.&nbsp;
